body:
Steps to Reproduce:

1.  When there is an invalid URL (put a space before https://) you don't get error checking in the user config

Here is my config in my user mcp.json
```json
{
	"servers": {
		"github": {
			"url": " https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/",
			"type": "http"
		}
	},
	"inputs": []
}
```

No errors:

<img width="1043" height="402" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/902730e2-9dd9-41cc-a734-55f75ff56454" />

however if i configure it in my vscode/mcp.json i get the error checks:

<img width="951" height="290" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c5e63142-e9a1-4341-be97-ab913115e1e1" />

Should be consistent here.
